{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C then grease and line base of a spring form tin (Ø 22 cm) with baking paper. Set aside.","Place almonds in mixing bowl and grind <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer to a small bowl and set aside.","Place ginger, 30 g sugar and orange peel in mixing bowl then grate <nobr>4 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and grate again <nobr>4 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then grate once more <nobr>4 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>.","Add butter, flour, 190 g sugar, reserved ground almonds, salt, baking powder and ground ginger then mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add eggs, milk and orange juice then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Pour one third of mixture into prepared tin then scatter over half the chopped rhubarb. Repeat then finish with a final layer of cake mix. Bake for 60-70 minutes (180°C), covering with foil halfway through if top begins to brown too much, until a skewer inserted in centre comes out clean. Allow cake to cool in tin for 10 minutes before turning out onto a wire rack. Serve warm or cold, cut in slices."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["80 g butter, diced, plus extra for greasing","200 g almonds","30 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)","220 g light brown sugar","1 orange, thin peelings of skin and 50 g juice","220 g spelt flour","½ tsp fine sea salt","1 ½ tsp baking powder","1 ½ tsp ground ginger","2 large eggs","200 g milk","300 g rhubarb, roughly chopped"]}],"id":"r103027","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-Biar6HgrCtM\/XZWrmEgsRUI\/AAAAAAAAfpo\/isp3zh2yhps6LdsbigP-DIi1kK0C5E-xgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_q3GMdZ3mVk1D6c4Z.png","title":"Rhubarb and Ginger Spelt Cake","publishedAt":"2016-05-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9.9 g","fat":"20 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"42 g","calories":"1621 kJ \/ 388 kcal"},"usefu